Patrisse Khan-Cullors (Left), Alicia Garza (Middle), and Opal Tometi (Right) were the co-founders of the #BlackLivesMatter project in 2013.
Through the #BlackLivesMatter, the movement has gained a significant amount of national attention and proudly celebrated its 6 year anniversary on July 13, 2019 of last year (Khan-Cullors).
As of May 1st, 2018, #BlackLivesMatter had been used an average of 17,000 times per day, and the raised issues predominantly addressed race, violence, and law enforcement (Chaudry 6).
The hashtag, #BlackLivesMatter, was created in the summer of 2013 when Alicia Garza tweeted about the case of Travyon Martin (Stephen, Bijan)
